  "texts": [
    "(37)This selection causes a 2.64% reduction in the total source counts, and a 1.18% reduction in the available sample for lensing.",
    "The origin of this selection lies in the previous lensfit version, which did not model the shapes for sources brighter than r auto = 20.",
    "The fraction of sources lost to this selection is relatively small (1.18%), and therefore we opted to keep this selection to be consistent with previous releases.Next we applied a resolution selection that is designed to improve weight and shape recalibration (Sect. 7.1.2): R < 0.9, (38) A170, page 32 of 54 where R is defined in Eq.",
    "This selection is a significant one, and removes 43.58% of the total MASK ≤ 1 sample.",
    "Of sources otherwise in the lensing sample, this selection removes 20.15% of the sources."
  ]
